833929766e-18,2.4544600286512048e-17,1.2285513163862873e-16,3.3611976263917244e-16,2.6307212825773804e-16,2.5701121142054427e-16,2.2182247382375487e-16,2.278502096325634e-16,6.192700909596225e-16,4.783176519752756e-16,5.749690471548403e-16,4.889795898181989e-16,1.945476101001656e-16,3.0451263580486705e-16,6.033110959694596e-16,6.112415926253086e-16,1.5132140684053916e-16,7.547658506504365e-17,7.812595984721893e-17,9.573933652856049e-17,2.328537428043507e-17,1.688313841448898e-16,1.0631108193068718e-16,8.328490801650477e-17,5.994570481686877e-17,1.3184886815078667e-16,2.635403277209611e-16,3.224522368756082e-16,7.492879861382943e-16,3.3798038574246257e-16,8.838501402253849e-16,4.895413101998529e-16,4.357148545228815e-16,2.3289114159935885e-16,1.6542916016282117e-17,1.3579514522619213e-16,5.094080788130028e-17,1.1661944547472127e-17,8.214749425871606e-17,8.161732900553592e-17,3.3185824048819614e-16,2.263990946556138e-16,1.4668910458890463e-16,8.087222063832221e-17,3.988355547534812e-17,2.1484217530612085e-17,8.847536072618122e-17,3.2375712580746977e-16,4.802625812901345e-16,3.534300222381455e-16,6.553172151510573e-16,6.314709623213599e-16,5.292820742725294e-16,3.8328687255765176e-16,2.287875536111686e-16,6.558039888787135e-16,4.098918766729167e-16,3.1932655416624525e-16,3.4044798726084036e-16,2.3191603739421735e-16,1.3131679440058021e-16,6.486958441784301e-17,2.3842264415488567e-16,2.1953710846971377e-16,1.2300385355772869e-16,4.525385883516787e-17,8.434225692716814e-17,1.6038644849767236e-16,3.106826226894363e-16,3.6091899909100784e-16],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"lines\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"crimson\",\"width\":1.5},\"name\":\"lines\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"One-Sided Magnitude Spectrum\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Frequency (Hz)\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Amplitude\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Round-Trip Verification\n\nA fundamental property: `np_ifft(np_fft(x))` should recover the original signal exactly (up to floating-point precision).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Round-trip: ifft(fft(signal)) should equal signal */\nrecovered : np_real(np_ifft(F))$\n\n/* Max absolute error */\nerr : np_max(np_abs(np_sub(signal, recovered)))$\nprint(\"Max round-trip error:\", err)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 34,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Max round-trip error: 7.771561172376096e-16"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Frequency-Domain Filtering [S+N]\n\nWe apply a low-pass filter by zeroing out FFT bins above a cutoff frequency. This is the simplest (ideal brick-wall) filter.\n\nSymbolically, the ideal low-pass filter has impulse response:\n$$h(t) = 2 f_c \\cdot \\text{sinc}(2 f_c t) = 2 f_c \\cdot \\frac{\\sin(2\\pi f_c t)}{2\\pi f_c t}$$\n\nIts Fourier transform is the rectangular function:\n$$H(f) = \\begin{cases} 1 & |f| \\leq f_c \\\\ 0 & |f| > f_c \\end{cases}$$\n\nHere we implement the discrete version directly in the frequency domain.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic: impulse response of ideal low-pass filter.\n   Use a concrete cutoff to avoid interactive assume() questions. */\nh_ideal : sin(2 * %pi * 30 * tau) / (%pi * tau);\nprint(\"Ideal LP impulse response h(t) =\", h_ideal)$\n\n/* Verify its Fourier transform at a frequency inside the passband */\nassume(tau > 0)$\nH_at_5 : 2 * integrate(h_ideal * cos(2 * %pi * 5 * tau), tau, 0, inf);\nprint(\"H(f=5) =\", H_at_5, \"(should be 1 for f < 30)\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 35,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "sin(60*%pi*tau)/(%pi*tau)\nIdeal LP impulse response h(t) = sin(60*%pi*tau)/(%pi*tau)\n1\nH(f=5) = 1 (should be 1 for f < 30)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Frequency-domain low-pass filter: zero bins above 30 Hz */\nf_cutoff : 30$\nbin_cutoff : round(f_cutoff * N / fs)$\nprint(\"Cutoff bin:\", bin_cutoff, \"out of\", N)$\n\n/* Copy FFT result, then zero high-frequency bins */\nF_filtered : np_copy(F)$\nfor k : bin_cutoff + 1 thru N - bin_cutoff - 1 do\n  np_set(F_filtered, k, 0.0)$\n\n/* Inverse FFT to get filtered signal */\nfiltered : np_real(np_ifft(F_filtered))$\n\nprint(\"Filtered signal: 50 Hz component should be removed\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 36,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Cutoff bin: 30 out of 256\nFiltered signal: 50 Hz component should be removed"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot original vs filtered signal */\nfilt_list : np_to_list(np_slice(filtered, [0, 128]))$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"steelblue\", line_width=1, name=\"Original\",\n  lines(t_list, sig_list),\n  color=\"crimson\", line_width=2, name=\"Low-pass filtered (< 30 Hz)\",\n  lines(t_list, filt_list),\n  title=\"Frequency-Domain Low-Pass Filter\",\n  xlabel=\"Time (s)\", ylabel=\"Amplitude\",\n  showlegend=true, grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 37,
      "outputs": [
        {
